The paper deals with scheduling problems, which are typically studied in the subfield of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of a PTAS (polynomial-time approximation scheme) suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of approximation algorithms (cs.DM). The consideration of energy consumption and speed-scaling cost suggests that the paper may be relevant to the subfield of information theory (cs.IT) or systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper's focus on scheduling and optimization suggests that it may also be relevant to the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG).
